In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 2011 as National Energy Action Month. He emphasizes the importance of taking bold action to create a secure energy future and build a clean energy economy. The Obama Administration has made significant investments in clean energy and aims to double renewable energy capacity in the United States by the end of next year. The administration has also implemented fuel economy standards for cars and trucks, increased the efficiency of homes and buildings, and established pollution reduction standards. President Obama calls on citizens to make cleaner energy choices to strengthen the nation, the economy, and the environment.